@berrybowl has been open for many years and it’s not a coincidence when you can serve healthy food at top quality in a creative way. Berry B. Does a great job and amid their selection of goodies your bound to create something that suits your fancy but if you feel overwhelmed they have a menu from smoothies to specialty bowls they can make for you right there! Like the Pitaya, Nutella, Tropical or Matcha bowls.🍵 You could even get a flight and sample multiple smaller size bowls. Berry bowl is delicious and when we say we could have this every morning to ease the stomach into the day, were not messin’ with you, it’s that tasty and refreshing. 👏 Berry Bowl is lucky to call coveted Highland Park home. Make sure to start you day here before you venture down York Blvd for the rest of the afternoon/evening. @berrybowl has been open for many years and it’s not a coincidence when you can serve healthy food at top quality in a creative way. Berry B. Does a great job and amid their selection of goodies your bound to create something that suits your fancy but if you feel overwhelmed they have a menu from smoothies to specialty bowls they can make for you right there! Berry bowl is delicious and when we say we could have this every day were not messin’ with you, it’s that tasty and refreshing. 👏 Berry Bowl is lucky to call coveted Highland Park home. Make sure to start you day here before you venture down York Blvd for the rest of the afternoon/evening. Like, comment or tag a friend who would love something healthy in the morning ! ✌️😎🥣🍇🍓🍌 #lafoodieguy #LAFG ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

Have you ever heard of Tejuino before? Tejuino is a cold beverage made from fermented corn and popularly consumed in the Mexican state of Jalisco and Chihuahua. (Wiki) The drink is typically thick in consistency and we’ve seen it garnished in a variety of ways. This one was pretty darn good but tejuino is usually a too thick for our pallet. And though it would make it a different drink, our touch would be adding some club soda, gingerale or sprite to make it a little more crisper with the carbonation. And maybe some tequila if we wanna get loose. 🕺Our favorite part is that they set up outside @churrosdonabel right on Whittier Blvd., which, if you haven’t been to Whittier Blvd., is a whole vibe. node.text:
Lomo Saltado Fries W/ Fried Egg || Inca Maya Tacos (@incamayatacos) || Van Nuys, CA

Video Credit 🎥: @lafoodieguy 

When you see a stand offering up Lomo Saltado, you gotta give it a try. And worth a try @incamayatacos is, to say the least. Tacos, burritos, they used to have breakfast, too, but the Lomo is a favorite and you can’t go wrong with a fried egg on top. These are the Lomo Fries but it’s close enough to the actual dish that usually mixes the fries with everything. AND, THESE are fresh cut fries – amazing. 🔥🥔 Lomo is perfect for breakfast or brunch, but Inca is only open nights currently. Go heavy on the green sauce because it’s bombleezy. 💣 Do you like Lomo Saltado?! Like, comment or tag a friend who loves Peruvian food! ✌️😎🍟 #LAFoodieGuy #LAFG #VanNuys

Pastrami Sandwich W/ American Cheese || Johnnie’s Pastrami || Culver City, CA

Photo Credit 📷: @lafoodieguy 

Johnnie’s Pastrami is as iconic as they come in LA and if you didn’t eat there growing up, oh well, there’s time now and it’s just as delicious as it’s always been. A little pricy, but you get what you pay for. Johnnie’s has been around since 1952, so you know they got to be doing something right. Thinly sliced hot pastrami, and always go American cheese for the added flavor and creaminess – truly a pastrami gem of LA. 🏆 Don’t forget to enjoy some of their homemade pickles and SPICY mustard with the sandwich! Have you been to Johnnie’s?! Like, comment or tag a friend who loves pastrami! ✌️😎🍔 #LAFoodieGuy #LAFG #culvercity

Shrimp, Potato § Cheesy Tacos Dorados || Mariscos Mazatleco (@mariscosmazatlecola) || Panorama City, CA

Video Credit 🎥: @lafoodieguy 

Taco Tuesday with some crunchy, cheesy shrimp tacos dorados from @mariscosmazatlecola in Panorama City! Don’t forget to add some of their homemade salsas for an added kick and definitely don’t forget an aguachile or ceviche tostada, too! 🐟 This truck is a go-to the day after a night out of drinking, IYKYK. Cold fish is so refreshing!📍Mazatleco also has locations in Palmdale and Van Nuys! Do you like tacos dorados?! Like, comment or tag a friend who would love these! ✌️😎🌮🦐 #LAFG #LAFoodieGuy #PanoramaCity
